cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a classifier to predict buying intentions based on user behaviour within an e-commerce website. This involves analyzing user data and extracting features from high dimensional data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with analyzing user behaviour, cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it involves studying user behaviour in an e-commerce website, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper may involve analyzing user data for security purposes, and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper deals with user behaviour within a website.
